<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311F1 Advisory Committee/1060:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-13T00:00:00+01:00">November 13, 1941—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received November
                                    13—8:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5432. Your 4867, October 31, 11 a.m. The Foreign Office informed me
                                that they had taken note of your message and had instructed
                                    Salter<note n="9" xml:id="d537fn9">Sir Arthur Salter, Chief
                                    British Representative at the renewed wheat discussions.</note>
                                accordingly. If you find difficulty in dealing with the wheat
                                situation, please notify me as I am certain that we can get
                                consideration and support of the position you outlined in your
                                message.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>